<subSubSection id="C328ABCEFFAE481F7BB0F9D2FE1F49E2" pageId="19" pageNumber="127" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFAE481F7BB0F9D2FEE74904" blockId="19.[189,324,1538,1564]" box="[189,324,1538,1564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="127">
<heading id="D0C54F29FFAE481F7BB0F9D2FEE74904" bold="true" box="[189,324,1538,1564]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="127" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFAE481F7BB0F9D2FEE74904" bold="true" box="[189,324,1538,1564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="127">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFAE481F7BB0F9E0FE1F49E2" blockId="19.[189,1400,1584,1787]" pageId="19" pageNumber="127">
The original description of the species mentions the presence of ridges ventrally on the pronotum and mesopleuron, a laterally wrinkled scutellum and distinct scutellar foveae, among characters regarding its coloration. The first are not useful enough to properly distinguish it from other similar species, and the characters regarding the coloration are mostly useless when talking about 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFAE481F7F6BF94AFB5249AC" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[1126,1265,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cynipoidea">Cynipoidea</taxonomicName>
. Thus, it is impossible to determine if 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFAE481F7AFAF96DFD1749CF" authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1951" box="[503,692,1725,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFAE481F7AFAF96DFD1749CF" box="[503,692,1725,1751]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="127">Aegilips notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a separate and valid species. Because of this, we consider it to be incertae sedis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
